Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with modeling the compositionality of words, which is a core topic in natural language processing. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a method to create visual embeddings for characters, which involves using a convolutional neural network. This is a common technique in computer vision. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to create character embeddings and evaluate their performance on a text classification task. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel approach to modeling character-level compositionality, which can be seen as a contribution to the broader field of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper evaluates the proposed method on a text classification task, which is a common application in information retrieval.
